  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1773194915" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1773194915" />
    <a title="Descending Angel" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/54467254-descending-angel"><img alt="Descending Angel" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1507399547p2/54467254.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1773194915?book_show_action=true">Oct 05, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Descending Angel" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Descending Angel" href="/user/show/54467254-descending-angel">Descending Angel</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/54467254-descending-angel?shelf=carter">carter</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1773194915" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6777013649052240416">Took awhile to get into the writing style which was expectedand then it just clicked and flowed beautifully. Alot of it is kinda a flashback/history of the Chance twins and it&apos;s interesting, it&apos;s funny and there&apos;s alot of casual incest and illegitimacy of children. The story is probably it&apos;s weakest part but it does enough. The characters and the classic Carter banter is really what makes this (her last novel) so good. </span>
  <span id="freeText6777013649052240416" style="display:none">Took awhile to get into the writing style which was expectedand then it just clicked and flowed beautifully. Alot of it is kinda a flashback/history of the Chance twins and it's interesting, it's funny and there's alot of casual incest and illegitimacy of children. The story is probably it's weakest part but it does enough. The characters and the classic Carter banter is really what makes this (her last novel) so good. </span>
